Classes of Function

The following mapping is given: \(f:A \to B\) with \(x\mapsto x^3+x^2+1\) for all \(x\in A\).
Its graph ist plotte below for values between \(-12\leq x\leq 12\):

Use the graph to decide whether the mapping represents a function and to which class of functions it belongs depending on sets \(A\) and \(B\).

(a) For \(A=\mathbb {R},B=\mathbb {R}\) the mapping is {1:MULTICHOICE:no function~a function~an injection~a surjection~=a bijection}.
(b) For \(A=\mathbb {Z},B=\mathbb {R}\) {1:MULTICHOICE:the mapping is~no function~=an injection~a surjection~a bijection}.

(c) For \(A=\mathbb {R},B=\mathbb {Z}\) the mapping is {1:MULTICHOICE:=no function~a function~an injection~a surjection~a bijection}.

The following mapping is given: \(f:A \to B\) with \(x\mapsto \sqrt {|x|}\) for all \(x\in A\).
Its graph ist plotte below for values between \(-12\leq x\leq 12\):

Use the graph to decide whether the mapping represents a function and to which class of functions it belongs depending on sets \(A\) and \(B\).

(a) For \(A=\mathbb {R},B=\mathbb {R}^+_0\) the mapping is {1:MULTICHOICE:no function~a function~an injection~=a surjection~a bijection}.
(b) For \(A=\mathbb {Z},B=\mathbb {R}^+\) {1:MULTICHOICE:=the mapping is~no function~an injection~a surjection~a bijection}.

(c) For \(A=\mathbb {R}^+,B=\mathbb {R}^+\) the mapping is {1:MULTICHOICE:no function~a function~an injection~a surjection~=a bijection}.

The following mapping is given: \(f:A \to B\) with \(x\mapsto \frac {x}{|x|}\cdot \sqrt {|x|}\) for all \(x\in A\).
Its graph ist plotte below for values between \(-12\leq x\leq 12\):

Use the graph to decide whether the mapping represents a function and to which class of functions it belongs depending on sets \(A\) and \(B\).

(a) For \(A=\mathbb {R}\setminus \left \{0\right \},B=\mathbb {R}\setminus \left \{0\right \}\) the mapping is {1:MULTICHOICE:no function~a function~an injection~a surjection~=a bijection}.
(b) For \(A=\mathbb {Z}\setminus \left \{0\right \},B=\mathbb {R}\setminus \left \{0\right \}\) {1:MULTICHOICE:the mapping is~no function~=an injection~a surjection~a bijection}.

(c) For \(A=\mathbb {N},B=\mathbb {R}\setminus \left \{0\right \}\) the mapping is {1:MULTICHOICE:no function~a function~=an injection~a surjection~a bijection}.
